make it little-endian only.<br /><br />The _worst_ thing to do is to make it some kind of "native-endian",<br />because then you have to deal with cross building issues etc.<br /><br />But using a __le32 type and just doing "le32_to_cpu()" is trivial and<br />optimal - not just because everybody relevant is LE anyway, but simply<br />because even if you _aren't_ LE, an unconditional byte swap is better<br />than a conditional native access.<br /><br />           Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
